      "content": "the problem is that those \"discrepancies\" look like systemic bias. we've had some pretty heavy pushback from civil rights groups saying the model is basically redlining through its data. because of the legal risk, leadership is considering pulling the plug on the ValuBot module entirely and switching to a manual review process to avoid a lawsuit. what's your take on that?",
